"title": "6026: sin, God's judgment on",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6026: sin, god's judgment on",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Sin comes under the judgment of God, in that it contradicts his nature and opposes his purposes.</p>\n<h2>God's judgment on sin</h2>\n<h3>God is the judge of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:21\">ISA 26:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:8\">PSA 99:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:11\">ISA 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:14\">AMO 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:12\">ZEP 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment is certain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:12\">ROM 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:38\">PSA 37:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:21\">PRO 11:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:27\">HEB 9:27</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment is in proportion to the seriousness of the sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:14\">JER 21:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:2\">DEU 25:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:18\">ISA 59:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:1-Matt7:5\">MAT 7:1–7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:47-Luke12:48\">LUK 12:47–12:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5-Rom2:6\">ROM 2:5–2:6</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment under the Sinaitic covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:5\">EXO 20:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:9\">DEU 5:9</a> <em>The Sinaitic covenant makes references to the judgment of future generations for the sins of their parents but, as a principle, this is abolished by later prophets.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:14-Lev26:39\">LEV 26:14–26:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15-Deut28:68\">DEU 28:15–28:68</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:29-Jer31:30\">JER 31:29–31:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:1-Ezek18:32\">EZK 18:1–18:32</a></p>\n<h3>John the Baptist and Jesus Christ warn of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:10\">MAT 3:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:9\">LUK 3:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:12\">MAT 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:19\">MAT 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:36-Matt12:37\">MAT 12:36–12:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42-Mark9:49\">MRK 9:42–9:49</a></p>\n<h2>Ways in which God judges sin</h2>\n<h3>God causes sin to bring evil to the sinner</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:23\">2CH 6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:19\">DEU 19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:10\">EST 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:15-Ps7:16\">PSA 7:15–7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:13\">ISA 30:13</a></p>\n<h3>God abandons people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:17-Deut31:18\">DEU 31:17–31:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:11-Josh7:12\">JOS 7:11–7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:16\">LAM 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23-Ezek39:24\">EZK 39:23–39:24</a></p>\n<h3>Unrepentant sinners to be expelled from the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:17\">MAT 18:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:13\">1CO 5:1–5:13</a></p>\n<h3>God exercises judgment through a country's legal system</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:3-Rom13:4\">ROM 13:3–13:4</a></p>\n<h3>Untimely death is God's judgment on all sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:17\">GEN 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:1-Lev20:17\">LEV 20:1–20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:13\">1CH 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:19\">PRO 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:32\">ROM 1:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:29-1Cor11:30\">1CO 11:29–11:30</a></p>\n<h3>Sinners are excluded from the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:15\">REV 22:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:10\">1CO 6:9–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:9-Gal5:21\">GAL 5:9–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:27\">REV 21:27</a></p>\n<h2>Occasions of God's judgment on sin</h2>\n<h3>OT examples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16-Gen3:24\">GEN 3:16–3:24</a> <em>expulsion from Eden</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:1-Gen7:24\">GEN 6:1–7:24</a> <em>the flood</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20-Gen19:29\">GEN 18:20–19:29</a> <em>Sodom and Gomorrah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:1-Deut9:5\">DEU 9:1–9:5</a> <em>The Canaanites (the Anakites were earlier inhabitants of Canaan).</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:7-2Kgs17:23\">2KI 17:7–17:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:10-2Kgs24:20\">2KI 24:10–24:20</a></p>\n<h3>The destruction of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:47-Luke11:51\">LUK 11:47–11:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34-Luke13:35\">LUK 13:34–13:35</a></p>\n<h3>God's final judgment of the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:24\">ISA 66:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:31–25:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:8–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:7\">JUD 1:7</a></p>",
